The paper deals with algorithms for approximating the girth and producing roundtrip spanners of directed graphs, which are fundamental problems in graph theory and have applications in various fields such as network design and routing. The paper uses techniques from computational geometry, graph algorithms, and numerical analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also involves probabilistic analysis and combinatorial optimization, which suggest the sub-categories cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as possible choices.
